issue.title: Enable estimate gas calls(non-precompile)

labels.name: limechain
labels.description: Work planned for the LimeChain team

issue.body:
This pull request enables the estimation of the approximate gas value that would be utilized in an eth_call transaction, specifically for non-precompile calls. The modifications are primarily made in the `ContractCallService`. 
Previously, the estimate gas logic within the web3 module wasn't available.

To determine the best gas cost, a [binary search](https://github.com/hashgraph/hedera-mirror-node/blob/90a378ef7f3ae6d5139a553420eba73f103d8e27/hedera-mirror-web3/src/main/java/com/hedera/mirror/web3/service/ContractCallService.java#L74) retry algorithm has been implemented instead of relying solely on the `gasUsed` value returned. 
**This algorithm has been adapted from the source code of [Metamask](https://github.com/MetaMask/web3-provider-engine/blob/160a57b394e3a1c7c27a6c2d235fd7b932be9292/subproviders/vm.js#L66-L106).**

Fixes #5498
